# Testing Structure and Environment Detection

## Environment Detection
The environment detection system is implemented in [detect-environment.ps1](mdc:.codespaces/testing/scripts/detect-environment.ps1) and provides:
- Docker availability detection
- Codespaces environment detection
- Container name resolution

## Test Scripts
The testing system is organized into modular components:

### Environment Tests
[test-environment.ps1](mdc:.codespaces/testing/scripts/test-environment.ps1) verifies:
- PHP installation and version
- Required PHP extensions
- Service connections (MySQL, Redis)
- Docker availability and configuration

### Codespaces Tests
[test-codespaces.ps1](mdc:.codespaces/testing/scripts/test-codespaces.ps1) validates:
- DevContainer configuration
- Service definitions
- Build scripts
- Dependencies

### Master Test Runner
[run-all-tests.ps1](mdc:.codespaces/testing/scripts/run-all-tests.ps1) orchestrates:
- Environment tests
- Codespaces tests
- Feature tests
- Report generation
- Checklist updates

## Test Results and Documentation
All test results are stored in:
- `.test/results/` - Markdown reports
- `.test/tracking/` - JSON tracking data
- `.test/checklist-tracking.json` - Test completion status
